column2: Migrated from EPA STORET Legacy Database- originally reported by Wisconsin DNR
Any information on the quality of lakes in relation to boating activities- including jet boats and jets skies. (letter sent to Laura 6/13/95) .
Lake color-clarity a little "cloudy" as summer progresses.
Heavy boat traffic 5/26 to 5/29. Clear blue light cirrus clouds- light breeze. Yellow pine fuzz is on the lake.

Blue sky with puffs of clouds. Rained 6/6 and 6/7 am. Slight breeze today with wavy surface. Pontoon with swimmers- fishing boat with 2 men. song birds singing- K9's barking- crows flying in distance- beautiful day to be on the H2O

Filtered sun. High colored clouds with patches of blue. Looks and feels like rain. Slight breeze out of the east.A loon flew over head towards east- cement truck backing up from sommerfeld property- DNR at boat landing- removing boat ramp and digging out- replace- H2O is still going down- we have a small beach at shoreline- can hear a horse- sheep- pig- etc sounds one of our dogs has the toy- finches at feeders- mourning dove just landed- took off due to dogs present- no boats or peope on shore- birds singing- calling buzzing around- has been a lot of green/yellowish bloom on our shoreline- especially after boating/skiing and towing activity.

Sunny- high stratus. Slight breeze- no waves - just a ripple. Cool- 50-60 degrees. Kayak and canoe on lake. Loons call yodels. Small birds. (gone one week) hear traffic- motorcycles- squirrels barking- green algae- small particles- numerous in lake- some bloom floating on northside of lake in bowl- shoreline water clear with a little lake foam on shoreline- a beautiful morning on the lake.

small fronts coming through with slight showers. Blue sky with high puffs of white. Large white thunder clouds west. slight breeze out of west- slight ripple- man on swim dock w/3 dogs getting a bath- no boats on the bowl- hear laughter of children east end- pontoons at docks- some covered- otherwise quiet.

5 days of heavy large motor jet skiing and towing over the fourth of July. A couple of fish boats on lake and 4 to 6 kayaks. 79 degrees. Sun out- high clouds- small cumulus cloud on W horizon- 3 loons on lake- soft breeze and ripples.

Light rain early. Sunny with cumulus clouds. Humid- heading for the 90's. Pair of loons- heron- swim dock and DNR boat.WDNR fire on jacket changing island signs- a water skier just getting set- slight occassion breeze- ripples.

Had 4 inches of rain in the last 2 weeks. 8/4 to 8/6 jet skis and larger inboard boats with water skiers and towing. Also had new boat that they ski and wake board on the wake: today sunny- white clouds- slight breeze-  w/slight ripples- couple boats towing appeared as going out and after we started- kids enjoying vacation- couple dogs barking- another glorious day
0.5 inches of rain 8/13. Windy- larger ripples and strong drift. Sunny- mid 70's. Feels like fall- loon wail in distance. A fishing boat leaving bowl- children on swim dock having fun

Blue sky with large white clouds. No wind- lake calm. Solitary loon. Rain last Friday and Saturday. Water temperature is 75 degrees. Hummers. a lot of "lake floor scum" on shore- styrafowm pieces from neighbors swim dock also on shore- (we're on east end) collecting side of lake- lucky us- but also great sunsets.

Sky blue with no clouds. Soft breeze. Pair of loons fishing. No activity on lake. Many swim docks in- some piers. Clumps of floor scum- white foam and small particles at shoreline- the "wakeski" boat out yesterday- but major boat traffic ended sunday 3rd Fall is in the air! 40F at night- mid 70F pm. "crock hunter" died 9/4- what a loss for all- animals-environment
beautiful- fall-like day. Sunny- no clouds. 70 degrees. Slight breeze with ripples. One pontoon going out- 1 fishing boat coming in.
Lake with mirror surface- overcast with dark clouds. No breeze. Has rained the last 2-3 days- rain expected this afternoon. 1 loon on lake. Quiet.
overcast with large dark clouds. Many rain showers this past week. Rained Friday and Saturday morning. Breeze and large ripples. Sun peeking through.
heavy frost last night. Light frost the past couple of nights. Dark clouds moving in.
43 degrees - temperature ten degrees below normal. Sunny- blue sky. Lake like a mirrow. Rain/snow past days. Yesterday heavy frost on trees.
sun-clouds moving in;H20=44 degrees- air=44degrees-quiet no activity on lake- eagle soaring
sunny- H20=54degrees air=64degrees;quiet- no activity on lake-
sunny w/lgr.white cloud puffs- slight breeze- H2O=66 deg.-air=80deg 3/4" rain Tues PM - Wed. AM  pine tree bloom on lake  quiet
air=58deg- H2O=65deg  blue skies w/white clouds; our "wake" boat is back!

column2: air=86deg- H2O=82deg last two days heavy boat traffic(both wake boats) inboards w/lgr motors towing and sking  7/2 major storm w/high winds- dangerous lightning lost transformer on north end of lake- heavy rain-our Sylvan fishing boat full of water resting on ground-and pea size hail. today looksand feels like rain- 2 loons on bowl of lake- 1 boat towing-fishing boat headed in with few drops of rain.alot of trash + weeds on shore along with lgr pieces of glass
air=78-H20=76 7/8 heavy rain/winds;rain early AM 7/9;lake calm w/slight breeze;no boats;cpl loons on bowl of lake;blue sky w/white clouds; plant fragments at shoreline

air=82-H20=78;moderate hunidity-praying for rain-sunny blue sky;little activity w/4kayaks-one sport boat towing 1 tube; blue heron on swim dock fishing;osprey soaring/fishing;2 loons;2 K9's playing at shoreline;calm and beautiful; 7/25 air=86;H20=84 humid 4:0pm- 15.75'-not bottom-low water-clear-blue;percept.=1 humid-sunny blue sky;6 kayaks-pontoon towing tubes- blue heron fishing- 2 loons grooming;female mallard w/4 near adult chicks; K9's "fishing" at shoreline

air=78- H20=83;clear blue sky- winddy w/smaller waves-no white caps;ski boat towing;sounds of lawn mower;children playing w/ dogs at sgore;54mph winds yesterday-limbs down- some bottom bog floating in from west thanks to boats-some shore foam-no humidity beautiful day except for the Milwaukee Brewers game

H20=78; air=80 sunny- very humid again-pontoon boat cruising;2 fishing boats;heron fishing from blind at cabin;:yellow pine boo extreme on shore line- visibility terrible; adults and kids swimming were yellow boo not present; our decoys and boats are getting stained yellow-worse I've ever seen concerned by sight of a pair swimming together and being informed of the new nesting sight by fellow lake people of  on a rock bar I decide to venture out in kayak to check things out with heavy heart. There has been a speed boat bombing up and down lake. Even though buoys were in place these people had no thought about the loons from past history. ir=80; H2O=78;sunny- humid again; pontoon boat;2 fishing boats; heron fishing at blind in front of cabin; yellow/green pine "poo" extreme at shore line; visibility terrible; kids swimming with adults on air matresses floating;boats and decoys stained yellow

air=72; H20=68; sunny beautiful day;windy so lake is wavy/ripples;pontoon boat cruising;speed boat towing sreaming children;people swimming around lake to cool off; jet ski- 7/3 finally had a break in the weather from cold/raining to July weather for the hoiday!; heron flying overhead; 2 loons pair was seen in large bay behind Donat Island while out doing secchi test. They dove and then on the way back to out cabin there were two loons close together looking "lpvingly" into each others eyes. They were both large but one appeared huge to me. We followed to get bandings on both birds.

column2: beautiful day so took another secchi. All very quiet on the lake and in the sky.

column1: Lke is up 8-10" with all the rain in the past weeks. Water at shore is once again clear and clean looking. I saw a couple frogs at shore that my lab enjoys chasing.
Good sign.

retrieved nesting buoys and placed them
male yodeling off in distance and saw female on the nest

column1: water still and released secchi disc to length of rope + another foot before lost sight of....our beautiful clear lake in spring did secchi test and then traveled shore of whole lake and found nothing to be concerned about

column2: air=65- H20=65  sunny- minimal boat traffic for holiday- fishing(Muskey ) boats towing- kayaks- a wake boat pulling skier; Loon Nesting buoys placed around Crane Island with one loon on west side relaxing on back; residents swimming(kids). Weather has been a challenge with winds/rain  but making the best of the days good weather. Saw a eagle attempt a attack on a heron mid air but heron wisely plummeted down into lake and escaped.
